-- Turkey's Bank Asya shares trade to resume on "watchlist" companies market
-- 
-- Fri Sep 26, 2014 07:19AM EDT
-- None



ISTANBUL, Sept 26 (Reuters) - Trading in shares of Turkey's Islamic lender Bank Asya <ASYAB.IS> was suspended on Friday due to volatility in the share price, Borsa Istanbul said in a filing.

Trading will resume on the watchlist companies market starting Sept. 30, the stock exchange said.